&lt;p&gt;I recently discovered something pretty remarkable: two of the open-source projects I started,
&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/IndEcol/country_converter"&gt;country_converter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://github.com/IndEcol/pymrio"&gt;pymrio&lt;/a&gt;, have been archived in the GitHub Arctic Code Vault.
This means that snapshots of my code are now stored on archival film, sealed in a vault 250 meters
deep within a mountain in Svalbard, Norway, designed to last for at least 1,000 years.&lt;/p&gt;
